14029b2b-2690-495c-aaae-2e0de2169065.title: Mourner
14029b2b-2690-495c-aaae-2e0de2169065.text:
I'm guarding the border to West Ardougne. No one
except we mourners can pass through

d3b04264-1379-4818-86be-1eb2142dde36.title: Mourner
d3b04264-1379-4818-86be-1eb2142dde36.text:
The plague of course. We can't risk cross
contamination.

options.text: What brought the plague to Ardougne?
What are the symptoms of the plague?

91b98c73-0913-46ea-99d1-3eebff82ba9d.title: <player>
91b98c73-0913-46ea-99d1-3eebff82ba9d.text: What brought the plague to Ardougne?

bf4a7a7a-0946-4b08-a692-6ca57deb9091.title: Mourner
bf4a7a7a-0946-4b08-a692-6ca57deb9091.text:
It's all down to King Tyras of West Ardougne. It
started came back from one of his visits to the lands
west of here.

72a60a6d-83cf-4900-a3ae-49dbc5cb1b9a.title: <player>
72a60a6d-83cf-4900-a3ae-49dbc5cb1b9a.text: Does he know how bad the situation is now?

99a92bf6-59fe-4bc7-8223-64ed98595d51.title: Mourner
99a92bf6-59fe-4bc7-8223-64ed98595d51.text:
If he did he wouldn't care. I believe he wants his people
to suffer, he's an evil man.

2f3ddcf0-3f45-4da2-9622-5041f16464e1.title: <player>
2f3ddcf0-3f45-4da2-9622-5041f16464e1.text: What are the symptoms of the plague?

568926d1-510f-4211-92c6-989e224566ea.title: Mourner
568926d1-510f-4211-92c6-989e224566ea.text:
The first signs are typical flu symptoms. These tend to
be followed by severe nightmares, horrifying
hallucinations which drive many to madness.

b6bb6a06-692f-4e1a-8591-222d88c2f61c.title: Mourner
b6bb6a06-692f-4e1a-8591-222d88c2f61c.text:
It gets worse. Next the victim's blood changes into a
thick black tar-like liquid, at this point they're past help.
